From nunchi-gate local patch series
Subject: feat(gateway): add channel-scoped display overrides for nunchi-room

This operator patch teaches Hermes gateway display resolution to honor
`display.channel_overrides.<platform>.<channel_id>.<setting>` before
platform/global settings, so nunchi-room can suppress tool/status chatter
without making all Discord lanes quiet.

Apply from `$HERMES_HOME/hermes-agent` with:
  git apply /path/to/nunchi/integrations/hermes/core-patches/0001-channel-scoped-display-overrides.patch

---
diff --git a/gateway/display_config.py b/gateway/display_config.py
index 58226ed48..c470cb05d 100644
--- a/gateway/display_config.py
+++ b/gateway/display_config.py
@@ -4,10 +4,11 @@ Provides ``resolve_display_setting()`` — the single entry-point for reading
 display settings with platform-specific overrides and sensible defaults.
 
 Resolution order (first non-None wins):
-    1. ``display.platforms.<platform>.<key>``  — explicit per-platform user override
-    2. ``display.<key>``                       — global user setting
-    3. ``_PLATFORM_DEFAULTS[<platform>][<key>]``  — built-in sensible default
-    4. ``_GLOBAL_DEFAULTS[<key>]``              — built-in global default
+    1. ``display.channel_overrides.<platform>.<channel_id>.<key>`` — channel override
+    2. ``display.platforms.<platform>.<key>``  — explicit per-platform user override
+    3. ``display.<key>``                       — global user setting
+    4. ``_PLATFORM_DEFAULTS[<platform>][<key>]``  — built-in sensible default
+    5. ``_GLOBAL_DEFAULTS[<key>]``              — built-in global default
 
 Exception: ``display.streaming`` is CLI-only.  Gateway streaming follows the
 top-level ``streaming`` config unless ``display.platforms.<platform>.streaming``
